#: ../../update-notes.rst:5
msgid "Update notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:6
msgid ""
"This section contains important information about Effektif system updates. "
"It lists changes to technical requirements for new versions and additional "
"instructions for updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:10
msgid "Updating to Effektif 3.4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:11
msgid ""
"Effektif 3.4 requires several infrastructure changes. Starting with version "
"3.4, Effektif requires Java 8. We also recommended upgrading MongoDB to "
"version 3.2.x, because of the increased performance and functionality. "
"Effektif 3.4 will still support MongoDB 2.4.x, but later releases will "
"assume that you are using MongoDB 3.2. Last but not least, Effektif 3.4 "
"supports Apache Tomcat 7 and 8. For now, you can use either version, but we "
"recommend the optional upgrade to Tomcat 8."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:18
msgid ""
"When updating Effektif and your infrastructure, follow the following "
"sequence:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:20
msgid "Update Java to Java 8 (required)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:21
msgid "Update Tomcat to Tomcat 8 (optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:22
msgid "Update the Effektif application"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:23
msgid "Update MongoDB to MongoDB 3.2 (required)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:25
msgid ""
"Be aware, the update to Effektif 3.4 contains multiple changes in the "
"underlying data schema which require several long running migrations. "
"Depending on the size of your database, the migrations might take several "
"seconds, or up to 20 minutes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:29
msgid "Updating Java and Tomcat"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:30
msgid ""
"The last Effektif release 2.27.x is already compatible with Java 8 and "
"Tomcat 8. Start by updating Java and Tomcat, because Effektif 3.4 will not "
"run on Java 7. You can install Tomcat 8 next to an existing Tomcat 7, and "
"then switch between the application servers. :ref:`install-tomcat` explains "
"how to setup a Tomcat 8 server. After the successful setup, ensure none of "
"the Tomcat servers is running. Then copy the ``$TOMCAT_HOME/webapps/ROOT`` "
"directory from your Tomcat 7 to your Tomcat 8 directory and start the Tomcat"
" 8 server. Now, you should be able to access the Effektif system again via a"
" browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:39
msgid "Updating Effektif"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:40
msgid ""
"As mentioned before, with the update to version 3.4 changes the data schema."
" Create a backup of your database before updating the application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:43
msgid ""
"Data migrations might take from several seconds up to several minutes. These"
" migrations are executed when the server starts, so the first start of "
"Effektif might take longer than usual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:46
msgid ""
"See :ref:`update` for more information on how to update the Effektif "
"application. After you have successfully updated Effektif, you can continue "
"with the next section and update MongoDB."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:50
msgid "Updating MongoDB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:51
msgid ""
"Effektif 3.4 now supports the latest version of MongoDB (3.2.x) which comes "
"with improved performance and functionality. The usual upgrade from MongoDB "
"2.4.x to 3.2.x (https://docs.mongodb.org/manual/release-notes/3.2-upgrade/) "
"requires a stepwise approach, first upgrading from 2.4 to 2.6, then from 2.6"
" to 3.0 and at last from 3.0 to 3.2. Upgrading the database also changes the"
" storage engine from the old MMAPv1 engine to the new WiredTiger engine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:55
msgid ""
"However, we will use a different approach to migrate your MongoDB 2.4.x to "
"version 3.2.x. This approach will simply import a backup of MongoDB 2.4.x "
"into a completely fresh setup of MongoDB 3.2.x."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:57
msgid "Stop the Tomcat application server - see :ref:`stopping`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:58
msgid ""
"Create a backup of your database using ``mongodump`` - see :ref:`backup`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:60
msgid "You will later import this backup into a new MongoDB 3.2 installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:62
msgid "Stop MongoDB - see :ref:`stopping`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:63
msgid ""
"*Windows only:* manually remove the created MongoDB service by executing "
"``$MONGO_HOME\\bin\\mongod.exe --remove`` with administrator privileges on "
"the command line ``cmd``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:64
msgid "Uninstall MongoDB 2.4.x, but ensure you don't delete your backup!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:66
msgid "*Windows:* Delete the MongoDB directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:67
msgid ""
"*Debian:* Use your package manager and uninstall the package ``mongodb-"
"10gen``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:69
msgid "Install MongoDB 3.2.x and recreate the Effektif database user again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:71
msgid ""
"``$TOMCAT_HOME/webapps/ROOT/WEB-INF/classes/effektif-onpremise.properties`` "
"contains the current name and password of the Effektif database user"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:72
msgid ""
"You can install the new version in the same place as the old one, please "
"ensure the data directory of the new database is empty before you start it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:73
msgid "Note that the the MongoDB configuration file format has changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:74
msgid ""
":ref:`install-mongodb` contains more information on how to setup MongoDB "
"3.2.x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:76
msgid "Start the new MongoDB instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:77
msgid ""
"Restore the backup partially to your new MongoDB instance using "
"``mongorestore``. Your backup from step 1 should contain multiple folders, "
"one for each database in the MongoDB instance. You only need to restore the "
"two that contain Effektifâ€™s data. Their default names are ``effektif`` and "
"``effektif-files``. You might have chosen a different name by defining "
"another value for ``effektif.mongodb.database`` in your Effektif "
"configuration file. The value there represents the name of the first "
"database and the name of the second database is generated by adding "
"``-files``. You have to execute the restore command for both of the "
"directories separately. The following lines show examples for the restore "
"commands, assuming your MongoDB user and database are both called "
"``effektif``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:79
msgid ""
"The database name is specified by the ``--db`` parameter and also by the "
"existing backup directory name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:80
msgid "*Windows:*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:82
msgid ""
"``$MONGO_HOME\\bin\\mongorestore.exe -u effektif -p <password> "
"--authenticationDatabase admin --db effektif C:\\path\\to\\dumps\\effektif``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:83
msgid ""
"``$MONGO_HOME\\bin\\mongorestore.exe -u effektif -p <password> "
"--authenticationDatabase admin --db effektif-files C:\\path\\to\\dumps"
"\\effektif-files``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:85
msgid "*Debian:*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:87
msgid ""
"``mongorestore -u effektif -p <password> --authenticationDatabase admin --db"
" effektif /path/to/dumps/effektif``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:88
msgid ""
"``mongorestore -u effektif -p <password> --authenticationDatabase admin --db"
" effektif-files /path/to/dumps/effektif-files``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:90
msgid "Restart Effektif and MongoDB - see :ref:`starting-effektif`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../update-notes.rst:92
msgid ""
"Your Effektif system has been updated successfully. You can now access the "
"Effektif application again via a browser."
msgstr ""

